curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/10062' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM8634", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM8634 is a quad, low voltage, low noise and  low power operational amplifier, which can operate from  2.5V to 5.5V single supply, while consuming only  470μA quiescent current per amplifier at 5V.  The SGM8634 features a 3.5mV maximum input offset  voltage. The minimum input common mode voltage is  within 0.1V below the negative rail, and the output  swing is rail-to-rail with heavy loads. It exhibits a high  gain-bandwidth product of 6MHz and a slew rate of  3.7V/μs. These specifications make the operational  amplifier appropriate for various applications.  The SGM8634 is available in Green TSSOP-14 and  SOIC-14 packages. It is specified over the extended  -40℃ to +125℃ industrial temperature range.  "}'
